<br>
I still don't.<br>
<br>
Could someone please tell me what is so special about this drink?  I'm sat here with a cup of it now and it tastes exactly like it smells.<br>
<br>
Why is everyone so enamoured with it?  I know it wakes you up (it has me, anyway) but other than that...  What is so amazing about it?  Does it grow on you or something?  Is there some magical process I have to put it through that causes me to be addicted to it for life?  Does it require a belief in seven Gods (best I can manage is one)?<br>
<br>
..I really don't understand it.<br>
<br>
~ Nick, PoBaka, intensely confused by the phenomenon known as coffee... <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=joltenclaw>JoltenClaw</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#A62A2A>(10/23/03 4:56 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm9.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2037.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Coffee</span><hr size=1> I go through the day in a daze unless i have 3 or 4 cups of coffee in the morning. Strong coffee. Stimulates my brain or something. <p>----<br>
