oving, and therein lies the danger: caffeine is addictive. Those of us who have to maintain a constant level of caffeine in our bloodstream to keep from falling over half-dead from a crippling caffeine-withdrawal headache will happily warn you of the dangers. If I haven't had a coffee or a soda by noon, I'm done until about 9 p.m.<br>
<br>
Now as for why else people like it, forget ye not the dangers of &quot;gourmet&quot; coffees. Or the coffee-based drinks being sold at coffee houses worldwide -- those taste much different from the coffee you're likely choking down right now. A shot of espresso mixed with some chocolate syrup and some almond-flavoured syrup and mixed with steamed milk is also considered &quot;coffee.&quot; And I drink one every morning. Between the calories and the caffeine, I'm likely killing myself, but it tastes so damn good I can't bring myself to give up my vice. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=gaspfv>Gasp FV</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>AKA Brevis</span><br> <font color=#A62A2A>(10/23/03 8:20 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm9.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2037.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Coffee</span><hr size=1> It's all about the caffeine content:<br>
<br>
12 ounce serving of Coke:  34.5 mg<br>
12 ounce serving of Pepsi:  37.5 mg<br>
12 ounce serving of Mountain Dew:  55.5 mg<br>
1 tablet of regular strength no-doz: 100 mg<br>
8 ounce serving of brewed coffee:  135 mg<br>
<br>
